## Introduction

This proposal outlines a comprehensive approach to building an **AI-powered OCR and Invoice Processing System** for **MostEdge**, in alignment with your goals of enabling real-time, scalable, and accurate ingestion of vendor invoices to support financial reconciliation, vendor intelligence, and automated reporting.

### ðŸ”¹ 3\. **Data Validation & Anomaly Detection**

### ðŸ”¹ 4\. **Database Integration**

- Use **MySQL** for structured product and vendor data.  
- Use **MongoDB** for storing invoice logs, OCR snapshots, and audit trails.

### ðŸ”¹ 5\. **API & Dashboard Publication**

- A **FastAPI** service will expose real-time APIs and serve data to internal dashboards (e.g. Streamlit).  
- Dashboards will provide operational visibility and reconciliation audit trails.

### ðŸ”¹ 6\. **Automation and Workflow Orchestration**

- End-to-end automation using **RabbitMQ** for modular parallel processing.  
- Decoupled services allow scalable throughput and resilience.

---

## System Architecture

The following diagram illustrates the complete solution architecture:

![][image1]

The system is broken down into:

- **Ingest Layer**: Accepts uploaded invoices or batch jobs. Optionally could include monitoring and extracting invoices from emails.  
- **Preprocessing Service**: Cleans and standardizes input files.  
- **OCR Engine**: Extracts key-value fields from diverse invoice formats.  
- **Postprocessing**: Normalizes and enriches output.  
- **Validation & HITL**: Flags anomalies and accepts manual review.  
- **Persistence**: Stores structured \+ raw outputs.  
- **API Layer**: Serves insights to dashboards and microservices.  
- **Monitoring**: Tracks uptime, accuracy, and system health.

---

## Technology Stack

| Component | Technology | Why This Tech? (Function & Purpose) |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Messaging Broker | RabbitMQ | Decouples services and enables high throughput parallelism |
| OCR Engine | Donut / LayoutLMv3 | Transformer-based invoice field extraction |
| Fallback OCR | Tesseract / EasyOCR | Backup OCR engine for difficult scans |
| Preprocessing | OpenCV / PIL / PyMuPDF | Image and PDF normalization |
| Validation Engine | FuzzyWuzzy / custom rules | Detect mismatches and anomalies |
| Relational DB | MySQL | Structured data storage (vendors/products) |
| NoSQL DB | MongoDB | Raw logs and snapshots storage |
| API Layer | FastAPI | Real-time invoice access |
| Dashboard | Streamlit / Dash | User-facing audit & status dashboards |
| Monitoring | Prometheus \+ Grafana | SLA tracking, alerts, observability |
| HITL Review | Custom React UI / Prodi.gy | Feedback loop for retraining |
| Model Management | HuggingFace \+ MLflow | Fine-tuning and versioning |
| Orchestration (Optional) | Apache Airflow / Prefect | Batch job coordination |
| Vector DB (Optional) | FAISS / Pinecone | Semantic enrichment & fuzzy match |
